Write a program that reads a user’s name and prints a greeting.

Prompt for two numbers, add them, and print the sum.

Accept a line of text and report its character count.

Convert string input to an integer safely (handle errors).

Ask for a floating-point number and format it with two decimal places.

Build a CLI menu asking for an option (1–3) and print the selection.

Read multiple space-separated integers and compute their average.

Prompt for a yes/no answer and handle both cases.

Show how to clear the input buffer and read again.

Explain why expect() is commonly used after read_line().
